INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3900','letter','1782-04-09','St Stephans','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I am informed that a Capt. Howell, in a N. W. cutter, has taken the flag schooner which Gen. Greene ordered to load with rice. I hope you have prevented her being carried away.','ltr_frm3900.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3901','letter','1782-04-10','','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','By the papers just sent me, it appears that Capt. Howell had the candles sold to the flag people, on purpose to have a plea of seizing her; you will, therefore, order the flag to sail immediately','ltr_frm3901.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3902','letter','1782-04-12','St Stephans','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','Doughty and Ancruni are not to do duty your way. I shall have such men returned as have served their month.','ltr_frm3902.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3903','letter','1782-04-12','','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I have received a letter from Gen. Greene. His orders are, not to suffer the flag schooner to be taken or detained. You will follow my orders respecting that business.','ltr_frm3903.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3904','letter','1782-04-13','','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','If you suffer Moore and Broderick to remain, they must give bail for their good behavior; each to give two good sureties, bound in five hundred guineas each, and to do six months duty in the militia','ltr_frm3904.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3905','letter','1782-04-18','Ferguson Swamp','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I have got thus far in my return from the Southward. I have been within eight miles of Bacon Bridge, and have had a hard march for no purpose.','ltr_frm3905.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3906','letter','1782-04-19','St Stephans','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','The Georgia refugees must do duty, if they have been in this State three months. No excuse to be taken for not doing duty.','ltr_frm3906.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3907','letter','1782-04-22','St Stephans','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','The flag must be sent immediately back, with all her cargo, passengers, attendance, goods, &c., &c., except Mrs. Shad, Mrs. Barnes and Miss Simmons, and their attendances and property','ltr_frm3907.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3908','letter','1782-04-24','St Stephans','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','Enclosed is a return of the companies which are to do duty in George town.','ltr_frm3908.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3909','letter','1782-04-24','St Stephans','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','James','Witherspoon','','individual','','Inclosed is a eommission to command the King\'s Tree Company, and hope you will accept of it ; and let no trifling matter induce you to refuse it.','ltr_frm3909.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3910','letter','1782-04-30','','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','Yours of the 26th came to hand. You may do as you please with Mr. Shad\'s daughter. Let Col. Moultrie have four rations.','ltr_frm3910.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3911','letter','1782-05-03','Bacon Bridge','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I am posted here, two miles in front of the Continental army, within three-quarters of a mile of the above bridge. The General, according to custom, keeps me between him and the enemy.','ltr_frm3911.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3912','letter','1782-05-11','Bacon Bridge','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','You will deliver all the horses you have, with the saddles, bridles, halter, and swords, except 14 of the ordinary horses which you will keep for your crops.','ltr_frm3912.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3913','letter','1782-05-20','Bacon Bridge','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I send you two letters addressed to Gov. Martin, which you will send by express that may be depended on it requires expedition. I send a letter for Ganey; please forward.','ltr_frm3913.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3914','letter','1782-05-21','Bacon Bridge','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I have information the enemy intends to make an attack on your post; you will order all the militia around you to your assistance.','ltr_frm3914.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3915','letter','1782-05-24','St Stephens','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','You must endeavor to seize Mrs. M\'s boat and negroes, and make prize of them, agreeable to the Governor\'s proclamation; a few men may do it easily.','ltr_frm3915.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3916','letter','1782-05-25','St Stephens','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','I am glad to hear the galley is got up. She must be fitted and manned for service as soon as possible, and stationed in the conflux of Waccamaw, Pee Dee and Sampit Rivers.','ltr_frm3916.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3917','letter','1782-06-02','Lynchs Creek','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','','Ganey','','individual','','The Colonels will give you a paper, in which you will find the determination of the British making peace with the Americans, which leaves you no hope of being supported by them.','ltr_frm3917.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3918','letter','1782-06-03','','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','','Ganey','','individual','','All such men will be allowed to go to Charlestown, and be considered as prisoners of war, to be exchanged for the American prisoners.','ltr_frm3918.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3919','letter','1782-06-09','Burghs','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','Yesterday, Major Ganey and myself signed a treaty. The principals are to submit it, and those who do not chose it are to be permitted to go within the enemy\'s lines with their wives and children','ltr_frm3919.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3920','letter','1782-06-12','Burghs','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','Provisions are so scarce here, that I am obliged to send boats down for rice. You will send by express thirty barrels, from whoever may have it, without regard of public or private property or engagements.','ltr_frm3920.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3921','letter','1782-06-15','Burghs','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','Enclosed you will find Gen. Greene\'s information of the enemy\'s intention.','ltr_frm3921.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3922','letter','1782-07-04','','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Peter','Horry','','individual','','You will procure as much rough rice as will pay the amount, giving a receipt for it on the public account','ltr_frm3922.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3923','letter','1782-09-24','Watbo','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','John','Matthews','','individual','','If you wish to stop all intercourse with the enemy, and prevent any supplies being carried into them, the position hinted for the General\'s cavalry is the only means to effect it.','ltr_frm3923.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_frm3924','letter','1782-09-24','Watbo','SC','US','Francis','Marion','','Nathanael','Greene','','individual','','I have certain intelligence that steps are still taken to evacuate, and am very sanguine it will take place by the 15th of next month.','ltr_frm3924.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Documentary History of the American Revolution Consisting of Letters and Papers Relating to the Contest for Liberty, Chiefly in South Carolina, from Originals in the Possession of the Editor, and Other Sources, 1776');
